==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Breech action
<hw>Breech action</hw>. <def>The breech mechanism in breech-loading
small arms and certain special guns, as automatic and machine guns; --
used frequently in referring to the method by which the movable barrels
of breech-loading shotguns are locked, unlocked, or rotated to loading
position.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

